(436, 26, 'page lead', 'Operating a local governmental unit always has challenges and opportunities. You may be looking for new efficiencies, projecting changes in tax revenue, finding new revenue sources, working on long-range planning, funding buildings and improvements, or structuring the most advantageous economic development package. Our years of experience in helping others in similar situations make us uniquely qualified to help you today -- and with tomorrow''s challenges.'),
(545, 251, '_wp_page_template', 'default'),
(544, 251, '_edit_lock', '1293093366'),
(543, 251, '_edit_last', '1'),
(437, 30, 'page lead', 'Quick deadlines? We''re used to them at UMBAUGH. In the world of economic development, quickly having the right response makes the difference between securing economic development for your area and watching it go elsewhere.\r\n\r\nWith most local governments'' tax revenues decreasing, economic development is the key to growing your tax base. But it''s not wise to say yes to every economic development opportunity that comes your way. You need to run the numbers, consider alternatives and make informed decisions about what''s right for your community to avoid overburdening your existing taxpayers or putting your investment at risk. UMBAUGH helps communities evaluate and structure economic development packages to produce long-term financial gain - not pain, using tax increment financing, tax abatement and the right balance of a variety of economic development tools.\r\n\r\nUMBAUGH''s economic development services continue long after the deal is done. We provide accurate financial data and reporting so you can make informed decisions about releasing tax revenue and leveraging your investment to generate additional development.'),
(438, 28, 'page lead', 'Governmental units are constantly seeking new, better and more cost-effective solutions to the demand for energy and other services. UMBAUGH takes a comprehensive approach that begins with constructing a customized financial plan for your utility. We then effectively and clearly communicate the financial plan to help you get the necessary support to make your plan successful.'),
(439, 32, 'page lead', 'At UMBAUGH, we don''t represent both sides of the table. We represent you as a school district. Our independence from the bond underwriting assures you of the greatest objectivity in analyzing, determining and planning - whether that''s for capital improvements or operatiing funds.\r\n\r\nWe quickly respond to your needs. At public hearings, we calmly, accurately and professionally answer all the financial questions your constituents - and your board - will have.'),
