(653, 3, '2010-07-07 18:37:05', '2010-07-07 18:37:05', '<div><em>Part 1 in a series</em></div>\r\nNow that July is upon us, local governmental units have started preparing 2011 budgets.  This series of articles will assist you with the complexities of transitioning revenue streams and the often-changing budgeting procedures.\r\n\r\nYour budget must be done on time without exception.\r\n\r\nThe deadlines from last year remain in effect for 2011 budget preparation.  Work backward from the November 1 adoption deadline and to give yourself enough time to meet all the target dates in the approval process.*\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>September 2 - Deadline for 1st publication</li>\r\n	<li>September 9 - Deadline for 2nd publication</li>\r\n	<li>September 17 (or at least 45 days before the taxing unit adopts its budget) - Deadline for submitting the budget to your County Council</li>\r\n	<li>October 17 (or at least 15 days before the taxing unit adopts its budget) - Deadline for County Council to review the taxing unit''s budget and issue its non-binding recommendations</li>\r\n	<li>October 19 - Deadline to file an excess levy appeal with the DLGF (excluding shortfall appeal)</li>\r\n	<li>October 22 - Deadline for public hearing</li>\r\n	<li>November 1- Deadline for budget adoption</li>\r\n	<li>November 3 - Deadline to submit budget documents to the County Auditor</li>\r\n	<li>December 30 - Deadline to file a shortfall excess levy appeal with the DLGF</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n* Note: This is the general timetable.  Exceptions and differences exist, such as for Appointed Boards and Special Districts.  Please refer to the specific budget adoption requirements for your taxing unit.\r\n\r\nIt is always a good idea to seek assistance or have someone take a second look at your budget before its adoption, especially in view of the current budget complexities.  If you have questions or need assistance in preparing your budget, please contact us.', '2011 Budget Calendar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '2011-budget-calendar', '', '', '2011-01-25 19:26:21', '2011-01-25 19:26:21', '', 0, 'http://dev.umbaugh.com/?p=653', 0, 'post', '', 0),
