(533, 3, '2009-07-08 19:23:58', '2009-07-08 19:23:58', 'Even though Umbaugh is a CPA firm, we don''t have a "tax season" because our practice provides financial advisory services for local governments throughout Indiana and Michigan. We do, however, experience a very intense time preparing Continuing Disclosure filings which typically are due June 30 of each year.  We recently assisted our clients with 173 filings coordinated by Susan Clark, the bond transaction group manager, and members of the Umbaugh Staff.\r\n\r\nContinuing disclosure requirements were first implemented in mid-1995 within SEC Rule 15(c) 2-12. This SEC Rule prohibits underwriters from purchasing bonds (with certain exceptions) unless the issuer provides  (1) annual financial and operating information  by a certain date, (2) timely notice of "material events," and (3) notice of any failure to provide the required annual disclosure by the deadline. The annual financial and operating data includes information that is most pertinent to the security of the bonds. In a property-tax-supported transaction it is a listing of major taxpayers, net assessed valuation, tax rates, etc. In a tax increment, revenue or income tax financing, the pertinent information regarding each of these revenue sources is provided.  The "material events" consist of the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Debt service delinquencies</li>\r\n	<li>Non-payment-related defaults</li>\r\n	<li>Unscheduled draws on either debt service reserves or credit enhancements (such as letter of credit or bond insurance)</li>\r\n	<li>Substitution of credit or liquidity providers, or their failure to perform</li>\r\n	<li>Modifications to the rights of bondholders</li>\r\n	<li>Bond redemptions or defeasances</li>\r\n	<li>Release, substitution or sale of property securing repayment of the bonds</li>\r\n	<li>Rating changes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGenerally, issuers with more than $10 million in outstanding debt are required to provide both the annual financial and operating data filings along with the material events notice.  These issuers are considered to be "large issuers" by the SEC.  These have previously been provided to National Municipal Securities Information Repositories (NRMSIRs).  The process was streamlined in 2004 to provide information to DisclosureUSA, which served as a central collection point.  Entities with less than $10 million in outstanding debt were required to provide a notice of any material events that occurred. These "small issuers" (as defined by the SEC) were required to provide financial reports only if specifically requested by the purchaser of the bonds.\r\n\r\nAll this is changing effective July 1.\r\n\r\nFor bonds issued after July 1, 2009, issuers with less than $10 million of debt, as described above, will be required to provide annual financial and operating data to EMMA (Electronic Municipal Market Access). This is data that was previously provided only upon request.  We recommend confirming with your bond counsel the interpretation of this requirement, but it is our understanding that the submitted data is intended to be the State Board of Accounts examination reports, CTARs, CAFRs or Form 9 (prepared only by school corporations).  Thus, the requirements of SEC Rule 15(c)2-12 have expanded to include entities with less than $10 million of debt outstanding.\r\n\r\nWe have assisted numerous issuers this past year with filing "material events" -- mainly due to rating changes, and bond redemptions or defeasances.\r\n\r\nEffective July 1, all Continuing Disclosure filings (for "large" and "small issuers") must be submitted to EMMA rather than to the existing NRMSIRs or DisclosureUSA. Continuing Disclosure documents will be accepted only in a portable document format (PDF). The EMMA website is www.emma.msrb.org. Filings will be available to the public within 15 minutes of submission.\r\n\r\n<em>If you have any questions about the transition to EMMA or other requirements of continuing disclosure, please contact us.</em>', 'May We Introduce EMMA? New Requirements for Continuing Disclosure', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'may-we-introduce-emma-new-requirements-for-continuing-disclosure', '', '', '2011-01-25 16:30:16', '2011-01-25 16:30:16', '', 0, 'http://dev.umbaugh.com/?p=533', 0, 'post', '', 0),
