(560, 3, '2009-04-29 21:23:29', '2009-04-29 21:23:29', 'The time frame for adopting any of the Local Option Income Taxes is April 1 to July 31.  This window of opportunity applies to CAGIT, COIT, CEDIT or any of the three LOITs.  If you have already adopted local income taxes and want to make adjustments, that also must be done during this same time period.  Any rate adopted or adjusted from April through July will take effect October 1.\r\n\r\nYou may find that you need to adopt a new tax or adjust current income taxes to make up for reduced property tax revenues due to Circuit Breaker caps and recessionary times.  Also, if you anticipate reduced revenue from local income taxes, you may need to analyze what is realistic in recessionary times. Please contact us at umbaugh@footnotes.com if you have any questions, need additional information, or if we can be of assistance.', 'Local Option Income Taxes - If You Want To Adopt One, Nowâ€™s The Time', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'local-option-income-taxes-if-you-want-to-adopt-one-now%e2%80%99s-the-time', '', '', '2011-01-25 15:35:14', '2011-01-25 15:35:14', '', 0, 'http://dev.umbaugh.com/?p=560', 0, 'post', '', 0),
