(577, 3, '2009-03-04 14:16:07', '2009-03-04 14:16:07', 'Third article in a series.\r\n\r\nAs predicted, the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 was passed and signed in February, and it contains an Economic Recovery Package â€“ or stimulus package â€“ with several provisions to help local communities rebuild their infrastructure â€“ bridges, roads and local water and wastewater systems.\r\n\r\nDetails are being worked out, and there is still much that is unknown about how much money will be available in Indiana and how the stimulus funds will be distributed.\r\n\r\nHere is what we know at this point in time:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you haven''t done so, enter your potential projects on the www.bsu.edu/cber Web site</strong>.  The deadline for entering projects or making changes is <strong>noon March 9</strong>.  This is not a grant application; it is a support and coordination tool, but it is important to enter your project information.  Include Indiana Department of Transportation projects as well as State Revolving Fund (SRF) projects.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Not all projects will be funded</strong>.  As of late last week, 6,800 projects had been entered and more are expected.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Priority will be given to projects that are ready to proceed, that leverage private investment and that stimulate job creation</strong>.  Most approved projects will still need to fund a minimum local match of 20 to 30 percent.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>No money is going to the State</strong>.  All monies will be distributed through existing federal programs which are very competitive nationwide.  State agencies such as Indiana Economic Development Corporation (IEDC) and the Indiana Association of Regional Councils will serve as subject matter experts, guide projects to the most appropriate funding sources and help maximize the amount of federal dollars flowing to Indiana.  (Note that stimulus money for schools has a different process and will be distributed to the State.)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>There will be a significant amount available for 2008 flood recovery programs</strong> if you are in one of the counties approved for 2008 disaster assistance.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>The analysis for potential projects will begin March 20.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nCommunities that want serious consideration should continue working to develop their project(s), because projects that can be implemented quickly will definitely have an advantage.', 'Deadlines Looming As Stimulus Package Details Unfold', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'deadlines-looming-as-stimulus-package-details-unfold', '', '', '2011-01-25 18:14:59', '2011-01-25 18:14:59', '', 0, 'http://dev.umbaugh.com/?p=577', 0, 'post', '', 0),
