(597, 3, '2009-11-11 16:26:30', '2009-11-11 16:26:30', 'In 2009 and 2010, the State of Indiana will provide replacement grants to school corporations throughout Indiana that will experience the greatest losses due to the circuit breaker.  A school corporation with a circuit breaker loss more than 2% of its levy is eligible for the state levy replacement grant. Originally, these grants were set to be statewide distributions of $50 million in 2009 and $70 million in 2010.  However, the most recent legislative session made some modifications, and current projections show up to $40 million to be distributed in 2009 and up to $60 million distributed in 2010.  However, to date only $90 million has been appropriated by the State of Indiana for such grants.\r\n\r\nIn 2009 we anticipate the grants to be allocated based upon the individual school corporation''s loss as a portion of total losses of eligible schools.  This same process will be applied in 2010, but each school corporation must first absorb the 2% levy loss, leaving the remainder eligible for the credits.  The State is expected to distribute these grants one time in the second half of the calendar year.  We do not know if these grants will be available beyond 2010.\r\n\r\nBased on the latest data prepared by the Legislative Services Agency, the following schools will be eligible for the state levy replacement grants:\r\n<table border="0" width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Alexandria Community School Corporation</td>\r\n<td>Mississinewa Community School Corp.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Anderson Community School Corporation</td>\r\n<td>Mitchell Community School Corp.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Attica Consolidated School Corporation</td>\r\n<td>Monroe Central School Corporation</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Avon Community School Corporation</td>\r\n<td>Mt. Pleasant Township Comm. School Corp.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Beech Grove City School Corporation</td>\r\n<td>Mt. Vernon Community School Corporation<